<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3044] thaiwordfilter uses attributesource.copyTo incorrectly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3044</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;The bug can be seen by &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/hudson/job/Lucene-Solr-tests-only-3.x/7367/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/hudson/job/Lucene-Solr-tests-only-3.x/7367/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like the issue is this lazy initialization of the cloned token: if the tokenstream is reused&lt;br/&gt;
and the consumer is interested in a different set of attributes, it could be a problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;one probably-probably-not-totally-correct fix would be to add &apos;clonedToken = null;&apos; to reset(), at &lt;br/&gt;
least it would solve this case?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
